  <body>
    <h1>FreeCodeCamp API Basejump: URL Shortener Microservice</h1>
    
    <h3>User stories:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>I can pass a URL as a parameter and I will receive a shortened URL in the JSON response.</li>
      <li>When I visit that shortened URL, it will redirect me to my original link.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Example creation usage:</h3>
    <p>
      https://req-header-parser-dishant15.c9users.io//new/https://www.google.com<br>
      https://req-header-parser-dishant15.c9users.io//new/http://foo.com:80
    </p>
    
    <h3>Example creation output</h3>
    <p>
      { "original_url":"http://foo.com:80", "short_url":"https://req-header-parser-dishant15.c9users.io//8170" }
    </p>
    
    <h3>Usage:</h3>
    <p>
      https://req-header-parser-dishant15.c9users.io//2871<br>
      Will redirect to:<br>
      https://www.google.com/<br>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>









